ge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20rescissions%20only%20take%2051%20votes%2C%20and%20the%20administration%20has%20said%20that%20this%20could%20be%20the%20first%20of%20several.%20That%20raises%20the%20possibility%20that%20Republicans%20could%20move%20to%20unilaterally%20defund%20Democratic%20priorities%20after%20government%20funding%20bills%20are%20passed%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20absurd%20for%20them%20to%20expect%20Democrats%20to%20act%20as%20business%20as%20usual%20and%20engage%20in%20a%20bipartisan%20appropriations%20process%20to%20fund%20the%20government%2C%20while%20they%20concurrently%20plot%20to%20pass%20a%20purely%20partisan%20rescissions%20bill%20to%20defund%20those%20same%20programs%20negotiated%20on%20a%20bipartisan%20basis%20behind%20the%20scenes%2C%26quot%3B%20Schumer%20said%20in%20the%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20lawmakers%20can't%20agree%20on%20how%20to%20fund%20the%20government%20in%20the%20coming%20fiscal%20year%20by%20September%2030%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwill-government-shutdown-happen-elon-musk-doge-whats-at-stake-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egovernment%20shutdown%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20take%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Republican%20senators%20have%20acknowledged%20the%20validity%20of%20Democratic%20senators'%20argument.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20get%20to%20the%20point%20where%20the%20Democrats%20look%20at%20this%20and%20say%2C%20'We%20can%20put%20it%20in%20the%20bill%2C%20but%20they're%20not%20going%20to%20fund%20it%2C%20or%20they're%20not%20going%20to%20use%20it%2C'%20then%20there's%20no%20reason%20for%20them%20to%20work%20with%20us%20to%20get%20to%2060%20votes%2C%26quot%3B%20Sen.%20Mike%20Rounds%20of%20South%20Dakota%20told%20BI%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20not%20every%20Republican%20is%20worried%20about%20the%20integrity%20of%20the%20current%20appropriations%20process%2C%20particularly%20those%20who%20remain%20concerned%20about%20high%20g