0shell%20with%20an%20extended%20range.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20startup's%20open-platform%20model%20licenses%20the%20design%20to%20governments%20for%20local%20production.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20an%20approach%20that%20challenges%20traditional%20defense%20procurement%2C%20aiming%20at%20agility%20and%20innovation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20weeks%20ago%2C%20a%20new%20defense%20tech%20startup%20stepped%20out%20of%20the%20shadows%20with%20a%20bold%20claim%3A%20it%20had%20built%20a%20radically%20advanced%20155mm%20artillery%20shell%20called%20Sceptre.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ammo%20quickly%20grabbed%20attention%20for%20its%20promised%20combination%20of%20unprecedented%20range%20and%20precision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20its%20creator%2C%20tech%20entrepreneur%20Chad%20Steelberg%2C%20believes%20the%20real%20innovation%20isn't%20necessarily%20what%20Sceptre%20does%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20how%20it's%20made%20and%20sold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Steelberg%20described%20Sceptre%20as%20an%20open%20weapons%20platform%3A%20licensed%20to%20governments%2C%20built%20locally%2C%20and%20updated%20like%20software.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20frees%20up%20Tiberius%20Aerospace%20%E2%80%94%20his%20startup%20%E2%80%94%20to%20focus%20on%20R%26amp%3BD%20rather%20than%20managing%20huge%20manufacturing%20contracts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20model%20born%20not%20in%20a%20defense%20industry%20boardroom%2C%20but%20in%20the%20logic%20of%20Silicon%20Valley%20and%20the%20battlefields%20of%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%94%20one%20built%20for%20speed%2C%20iteration%2C%20and%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20proposal%20is%20a%20radical%20step%20away%20from%20the%20highly%20centralized%2C%20slow-moving%20defense%20industrial%20base%20and%20contracting%20and%20acquisition%20processes%20that%20the%20Pentagon%20and%20other%20Western%20countries%20are%20wedded%20to%2C%20and%20it's%20sparked%20a%20mixture%20of%20curiosity%20and%20skepticism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ccd31c07-602c-4a7e-812a-43bdb19a44c8%5C%22%3EA%20founder%20with%20a%20mission%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%202024%2C%20sickened%20by%20the%20Russian%20onslaught%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20Steelberg%20made%20a%20decision.%20He%20stepped%20down%20as%20CEO%20of%20the%20AI%20firm%20he%20had%20cofounded%2C%20Veritone%2C%20and%20handed%20the%20keys%20to%20his%20No.2.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20gave%20them%20four%20months'%20notice%26quot%3B%20before%20founding%20Tiberius%20Aerospace%2C%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20knew%20nothing%20about%20aerospace%20back%20then%2C%20he%20said.%20But%20he%20knew%20people%20who%20did%2C%20bringing%20in%20a%20Navy%20SEAL%20commander%2C%20a%20former%20Apple%20hardware%20lead%2C%20and%20a%20top%20engineer%20from%20Raytheon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20get%20the%20best%20people%20in%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Steelberg%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20put%20'em%20in%20a%20room%2C%20lock%20the%20box%2C%20and%20say%3A%20let's%20solve%20this%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20led%20to%20Sceptre%2C%20a%20rocket-propelled%20155mm%20artillery%20shell%20that%20Steelberg%20says%20can%20hit%20targets%20up%20to%2095%20miles%20away%E2%80%94%20nearly%20triple%20the%20range%20of%20standard%20rounds%20%E2%80%94%20with%20precision%2C%20even%20in%20GPS-denied%20environments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20munition%20itself%20has%20undergone%20test%20firing%20on%20a%20M777%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20side-by-side%20graphic%20of%20Tiberius%20Aerospace's%20Sceptre%2C%20a%20155mm%20shell%20prototype%2C%20seen%20with%20wings%20retracted%20and%20out.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68666f43f748d8c055f4e7d5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22834%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20side-by-side%20graphic%20of%20Tiberius%20Aerospace's%20Sceptre%2C%20a%20155mm%20shell%20prototype%2C%20seen%20with%20wings%20retracted%20and%20out.%3Cp%3ETiberius%20Aerospace%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20its%20differences%20from%20standard%20rounds%20(those%20without%20rocket%20assist)%20%E2%80%94%20which%20have%20a%20range%20of%20about%2015%20miles%20and%20require%20add-ons%20for%20rocket%20propulsion%20and%20precision%20guidance%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20a%20category-defying%20munition%20more%20comparable%20to%20an%20extended-range%20GMLRS.%20But%2C%20like%20the%20original%20155mm%20round%2C%20it's%20fired%20from%20a%20howitzer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20artillery%20battles%2C%20range%20is%20critical%3B%20after%20all%2C%20that's%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20the%20HIMARS%2C%20a%20rocket%20artillery%20system%2C%20was%20so%20effective%20when%20it%20initially%20arrived%20in%20Ukraine%3A%20it%20gave%20Kyiv's%20forces%20much-needed%20reach%20in%20combat.%20Steelberg%20says%20it%20will%20%26quot%3Bchange%20the%20balance%20of%20power%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20Ukrainian%20battlefield%20and%20beyond%2C%20though%20it%20would%20need%20to%20be%20widely%20fielded%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220d5c62f3-7ec2-49da-8757-98235ed6558b%5C%22%3ESupplanting%20old-school%20procurement%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETiberius%20won't%20actually%20be%20manufacturing%20Sceptre%2C%20offering%20an%20unusual%20%26quot%3Bdefense-as-a-service%26quot%3B%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20plans%20to%20license%20the%20design%20to%20governments%2C%20which%20will%20pay%20%245%20million%20upfront%20to%20gain%20manufacturing%20rights%2C%20and%20then%20%242.5%20million%20a%20year%20to%20stay%20on%20board%20and%20get%20continual%20updates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20can%20then%20produce%20the%20munition%20in-country%2C%20using%20their%20own%20supply%20chains%20and%20industrial%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20makes%20this%20possible%20is%20Tiberius%20opening%20up%20its%20specifications%20for%20individual%20components%20%E2%80%94%20like%20batteries%2C%20guidance%20units%2C%20and%20fuel%20systems%20%E2%80%94%20to%20outside%20suppliers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteelberg%20said%20suppliers%20will%20be%20encouraged%20to%20propose%20improvements%2C%20as%20long%20as%20the%20component%20fits%20within%20Sceptre's%20volumetric%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20certify%20it%2C%20test%20it%2C%20fire%20it%20on%20the%20range%2C%20qualify%20it%20as%20a%20version%20if%20it%20passes%20safety%20and%20efficacy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20creates%20competition%20and%20choice%20for%20the%20governments%20buying%20it%2C%20he%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20model%20inspired%20by%20the%20early%20days%20of%20Intel%2C%20leaning%20on%20an%20open%20architecture%2C%20Steelberg%20said.%20While%20major%20companies%20like%20Boeing%20regularly%20bring%20in%20subcontractors%20to%20provide%20parts%2C%20Tiberius'%20platform%20is%20built%20around%20encouraging%20an%20ongoing%20ecosystem%20around%20this%20logic%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0almost%20like%20an%20app%20store%20for%20defence%20tech%2C%20with%20Sceptre%20at%20its%20core.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20suggested%20this%20would%20give%20governments%20the%20freedom%20to%20choose%20small%2C%20nimble%20manufacturers%2C%20support%20their%20own%20defense%20ecosystems%2C%20and%20reduce%20reliance%20on%20a%20handful%20of%20major%20contractors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGovernments%20place%20an%20order%20%E2%80%94%20keeping%20the%20intellectual%20property%20%E2%80%94%20for%20the%20version%20of%20Sceptre%20they%20end%20up%20making.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bulk%20of%20Sceptre's%20main%20parts%20can%20be%20manufactured%20on%20simple%2C%20widely%20available%20CNC%20machines.%20This%2C%20Steelberg%20argues%2C%20cuts%20out%20the%20need%20for%20much%20of%20the%20heavy-duty%20facilities%20typically%20involved%20in%20munitions%20production%20and%20opens%20it%20up%20to%20much%20smaller%20players.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20now%20they're%20actually%20allocating%20dollars%20to%20support%20not%20just%20the%20end%20weapon%20they're%20looking%20for%2C%20but%20actually%20the%20industries%20and%20the%20providers%20that%20manufactured%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20result%2C%20in%20his%20view%2C%20is%20a%20system%20that's%20more%20agile%2C%20more%20resilient%2C%20and%20better%20suited%20to%20modern%20warfare%2C%20where%20needs%20change%20faster%20than%20traditional%20procurement%20can%20keep%20up%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22029c1a9c-d041-40af-8093-7957ee249411%5C%22%3EA%20global%20procurement%20quagmire%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20NATO%20countries%20scramble%20to%20rebuild%20their%20arsenals%2C%20the%20limits%20of%20the%20traditional%20procurement%20system%20are%20becoming%20harder%20to%20ignore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20terms%20of%20ammunition%2C%20Russia%20produces%20in%20three%20months%20what%20the%20whole%20of%20NATO%20produces%20in%20a%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20NATO%20secretary-general%2C%20Mark%20Rutte%2C%20warned%20recently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20Urals%20Vladimir%20Putin%20tanks%20armored%20vehicles%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5c6ec5071631a302ac3769c5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22952%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPutin%20has%20ramped%20up%20military%20production.%3Cp%3ESputnik%2FAlexei%20Nikolskyi%2FKremlin%2FFile%20Photo%20via%20REUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAutocratic%20regimes%20like%20Russia's%20can%20command%20industry%20at%20will.%20Democracies%20can't%20%E2%80%94%20and%20procurement%20systems%20built%20for%20peacetime%20tend%20to%20move%20at%20a%20glacial%20pace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20broad-brush%20terms%3A%20a%20government%20commissions%20a%20giant%20contractor%2C%20a%20timeline%20and%20price%20are%20agreed%2C%20and%20five%2C%20ten%2C%20twenty%20years%20later%2C%20a%20product%20rolls%20off%20the%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20model%20shuts%20out%20smaller%20players%20almost%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20big%2C%20big%20problem%20honestly%20is%20that%20there's%20been%20a%20co-evolution%20of%20ministries%20of%20defense%20and%20big%20prime%20manufacturers%2C%26quot%3B%20Steelberg%20said%2C%20describing%20it%20as%20%26quot%3Ban%20intellectual%20and%20contractual%20moat%20that%20prevents%20anyone%20else%20from%20getting%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20known%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmilitary-challenges-drones-marine-corps-modern-day-marine-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20%26quot%3Bvalley%20of%20death%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20few%20new%20players%20can%20easily%20navigate%20Pentagon%20bureaucracy%2C%20or%20can%20bank%20on%20being%20around%20long%20enough%20to%20secure%20a%20contract.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDOD%20is%20experimenting%20with%20newer%20and%20nimbler%20models%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20open%20platforms%20and%20schemes%20to%20partner%20with%20smaller%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20but%20nothing%20quite%20to%20the%20scale%20that%20Tiberius%20envisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaul%20Hough%2C%20a%20UK-based%20expert%20in%20defense%20procurement%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.exeter.ac.uk%2Fv8media%2Fresearch%2Ffacilities%2Fpolicy%2FINDUSTRIAL_STRATEGY_FOR_DEFENCE_Paul_Hough_(1).pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshares%20Steelberg's%20calls%20for%20a%20shake-up%20of%20the%20system%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBefore%20we%20start%20pushing%20tsunamis%20of%20money%20through%20the%20old%20procurement%20model%20and%20the%20old%20industrial%20base%20structure%2C%20we%20should%20stop%2C%20take%20a%20breath%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20yawning%20gap%20between%20promising%20prototypes%20from%20small%20companies%20and%20actual%20military%20adoption%20is%20further%20complicated%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20innovation%20increasingly%20comes%20from%20the%20private%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201960s%2C%20governments%20funded%20around%2060%25%20of%20global%20R%26amp%3BD%2C%20according%20to%20Casey%20Purley%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Pentagon's%20Army%20Applications%20Laboratory.%20Today%2C%20she%20says%20it's%20about%2020%25%2C%20with%20commercial%20firms%20%E2%80%94%20often%20tech%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20picking%20up%20the%20slack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20AI%20to%20robotics%2C%20we%20need%20to%20work%20with%20companies%20we%20historically%20haven't%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20a%20recent%20conference%20in%20London.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e1d37a30-58b4-4a31-a695-fc129551b6b9%5C%22%3EQuality%20control%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECynthia%20Cook%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Defense-Industrial%20Initiatives%20Group%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%2C%20said%20that%20Steelberg's%20model%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20have%20the%20potential%20for%20production%20where%20some%20parts%20are%20made%20by%20primarily%20commercial%20suppliers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20could%20be%20a%20way%20of%20engaging%20the%20full%20industrial%20base%20beyond%20the%20more%20narrow%20slice%20of%20companies%20that%20are%20understood%20to%20be%20defense%20contractors%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECapt.%20Bradley%20Martin%2C%20a%20RAND%20researcher%20who%20specializes%20in%20supply%20chain%20security%2C%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bmuch%20of%20the%20barrier-to-entry%20problem%20is%20solved%20because%20a%20company%20is%20only%20providing%20a%20small%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20other%20issues%20deserve%20scrutiny%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Tiberius%20plans%20to%20take%20charge%20of%20certifying%20components%2C%20quality%20assurance%20could%20prove%20cumbersome%2C%20Martin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20major%20issue%20will%20be%20tracking%20the%20provenance%20of%20materials%20used%20by%20the%20companies%20supplying%20components%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20a%20company's%20normal%20supply%20chain%20is%20heavily%20China-based%2C%20we%20would%20be%20creating%20a%20vulnerability%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d8534817-c428-41a3-90af-44f723c682bb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESurge%20production%20vs%20just-in-time%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US's%20standard-issue%20155mm%20shells%20are%20manufactured%20by%20government-owned%20facilities%2C%20so%20production%20can%20lay%20dormant%20but%20be%20surged%20relatively%20easily.%20That's%20not%20really%20the%20case%20for%20non-standard%20shells.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20companies%20in%20the%20US%20are%20not%20dedicated%20to%20producing%20parts%20for%20Sceptre%20and%20move%20out%20of%20the%20business%20due%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20contracts%2C%20they'll%20%26quot%3Bneed%20to%20be%20attracted%20back%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20may%20have%20other%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Cook%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20walks%20past%20piles%20of%20155mm%20shells%20on%20wooden%20pallets%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F685bdedd3d5881a51c1c0898%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E155mm%20shells%20being%20produced%20at%20a%20factory%20in%20France.%3Cp%3ELionel%20BONAVENTURE%20%2F%20AFP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHough%20said%20that%20Sceptre%20may%20be%20cheaper%20and%20faster%20to%20produce%20in%20small%20batches%2C%20but%20he%20argued%20that%20it%20misses%20the%20broader%20context.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArtillery%20is%20still%20primarily%20an%20area-effect%20weapon%2C%20he%20said.%20The%20heavy%20weapons%20are%20indirect%20fire%20capabilities%20used%20for%20wide%20destruction%20and%20suppression%2C%20so%20while%20there%20is%20a%20place%20for%20the%20exquisite%2C%20precision-guided%20munitions%2C%20unless%20doctrine%20changes%2C%20precision%20rounds%20%26quot%3Bare%20unlikely%20to%20supplant%20area%20(dumb)%20rounds%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHough%20said%20that%2C%20after%20Ukraine%2C%20militaries%20are%20prioritizing%20large%20stockpiles%20over%20just-in-time%20flexibility%20%E2%80%94%20a%20trend%20that%20doesn't%20appear%20to%20align%20with%20Tiberius'%20more%20agile%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20some%20stages%20of%20shell%20production%2C%20including%20when%20explosives%20are%20inserted%20into%20the%20casing%2C%20are%20also%20%26quot%3Bnot%20a%20trivial%20exercise%26quot%3B%20and%20favor%20longer%2C%20centralized%20production%20runs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Hough%2C%20Tiberius'%20licensing%20model%20may%20be%20best%20used%20by%20the%20military%20in%20the%20same%20field%20from%20which%20Steelberg%20took%20his%20inspiration%20%E2%80%94%20software.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20hope%20that%20the%20Tiberius%20model%20works%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20at%20this%20point%20it%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20novel%20potential%20addition%20rather%20than%20a%20fundamental%20change%20to%20the%20established%20supply%20chain.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhatever%20happens%2C%20though%2C%20he%20added%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20do%20need%20people%20that%20challenge%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Steelberg%2C%20his%20mission%20is%20one%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Einspired%20by%20Winston%20Churchill's%20famous%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspeeches-that-changed-the-world-2016-3%23winston-churchill--blood-toil-tears-and-sweat-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bblood%2C%20toil%2C%20tears%20and%20sweat%26quot%3B%20speech%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20for%20him%2C%20enough%20blood%20and%20tears%20have%20been%20spilled%20already.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20absolutely%20am%20willing%20to%20give%20you%20my%20toil%20and%20my%20sweat%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20But%20if%20the%20West%20doesn't%20resolve%20its%20procurement%20issues%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20will%20be%20spilling%20our%20blood%20and%20our%20tears.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-tech-ceo-wants-break-open-defense-procurement-tiberius-sceptre-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20I