Texas%20voted%20to%20incorporate%20the%20area%20around%20a%20SpaceX%20complex%20as%20the%20city%20of%20%26quot%3BStarbase%26quot%3B%20in%20May%202025.%20The%20city%20is%20designed%20around%20the%20Starship%20rocket%2C%20which%20Musk%20hopes%20will%20eventually%20bring%20humans%20to%20Mars.%20Company%20employees%20and%20their%20families%20make%20up%20nearly%20all%20of%20the%20500%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20everything%20to%20know%20about%20Starbase's%20founding%2C%20leadership%20and%20population%2C%20and%20controversy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2231f00cd1-316b-4109-ac5d-8d486785f7eb%5C%22%3EStarbase%20has%20been%20years%20in%20the%20making%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20late%202010s%2C%20Musk%20decided%20that%20Texas%20was%20a%20friendlier%20place%20to%20do%20business%20than%20California%2C%20and%20by%202020%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsatellite-photos-show-elon-musk-growing-texas-empire-spacex-tesla-2025-4%23space-x-bought-land-in-texas-in-2012-near-boca-chica-village-the-small-community-near-the-mexico-border-had-about-30-homes-back-then-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoving%20some%20company%20headquarters%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Lone%20Star%20State.%20SpaceX%20bought%20land%20to%20manufacture%20and%20test%20Starship%20rockets%20in%202012%20near%20Boca%20Chica%20Village%2C%20a%20remote%20coastal%20area%20close%20to%20the%20border%20with%20Mexico.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20there%20were%20about%2030%20homes%20there.%20The%20company%20announced%20it%20had%20chosen%20the%20site%20for%20its%20Starship%20program%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elon%20Musk%20also%20named%20a%20town%20in%20Boca%20Chica%2C%20Texas%20%26quot%3BStarbase.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6425c45bed593e00183f4894%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22681%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESpaceX%20announced%20it%20would%20launch%20Starship%20rockets%20from%20Starbase%20in%202014.%3Cp%3EJIM%20WATSON%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rocket%20company%20needed%20to%20make%20room%20for%20Starbase%2C%20its%20new%20rocket%20launch%20site%2C%20and%20tried%20to%20buy%20out%20the%20locals.%20SpaceX%20told%20some%20residents%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20safe%26quot%3B%20to%20live%20there.%20Some%20packed%20up%2C%20some%20stayed%2C%20all%20while%20SpaceX%20employees%20moved%20into%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20first%20floated%20the%20idea%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-starbase-city-spacex-texas-launch-site-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eincorporating%20Starbase%20as%20a%20city%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20officials%20in%20Cameron%20County%2C%20Texas%2C%20in%202021.%20In%20December%202024%2C%20the%20company%20submitted%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-wants-to-turn-spacexs-texas-starbase-own-city-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epetition%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20local%20authorities%20asking%20for%20an%20election%20to%20incorporate%20the%20launch%20site%20as%20a%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELess%20than%20a%20year%20later%2C%20that%20election%20came%20to%20pass.%20On%20May%203%2C%202025%2C%20residents%20around%20the%20SpaceX%20complex%20voted%20almost%20unanimously%20to%20incorporate%20the%20area%20as%20the%20city%20of%20Starbase.%20The%20final%20tally%20came%20out%20to%20212%20votes%20in%20favor%20to%206%20against%2C%20according%20to%20county%20election%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22847ad397-d78c-441b-98a0-fcdc358aa662%5C%22%3ESpaceX%20employees%20lead%20Starbase%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20around%20500%20people%20live%20in%20Starbase%2C%20most%20of%20whom%20are%20families%20of%20the%20about%20260%20SpaceX%20employees%20who%20are%20residents.%20Musk%20has%20a%20home%20in%20Starbase.%20In%202021%2C%20he%20said%20on%20X%20that%20his%20primary%20residence%20is%20a%20%26quot%3B~%2450k%20house%20in%20Boca%20Chica%20%2F%20Starbase%20that%20I%20rent%20from%20SpaceX.%26quot%3B%20He%20is%20also%20registered%20to%20vote%20in%20the%20area%20and%20posted%20a%20picture%20of%20himself%20voting%20in%20Cameron%20County%20ahead%20of%20the%202024%20presidential%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20more%20than%203%2C000%20people%20who%20work%20out%20of%20Starbase%20commute%20each%20day%20in%20and%20drive%20past%20a%20nine-foot%20golden%20bust%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-net-worth%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMusk%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20their%20way%20into%20the%20facility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223456%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elon%20Musk%20bust%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686fdc6685e81483682dc1b2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225184%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20bust%20of%20Elon%20Musk%20lines%20the%20road%20leading%20to%20Starbase.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Skipper%2FREUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStarbase's%20elected%20officials%20are%20all%20current%20or%20former%20SpaceX%20staff.%20Bobby%20Peden%20ran%20unopposed%20for%20mayor%20and%20got%20216%20votes.%20He%20has%20been%20at%20SpaceX%20for%20more%20than%2012%20years%20and%20is%20currently%20the%20%26quot%3BVP%20-%20Texas%20Test%20%26amp%3B%20Launch%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20his%20LinkedIn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJordan%20Buss%20and%20Jenna%20Petrzelka%20are%20commissioners.%20They%20serve%20as%20SpaceX's%20senior%20director%20of%20environmental%20health%20and%20safety%20and%20former%20operations%20engineering%20manager%2C%20respectively.%20According%20to%20the%20city's%20website%2C%20Buss%20joined%20SpaceX%20in%202023%2C%20and%20Petrzelka%20in%202012.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2222a474c9-38ae-4783-adf3-ab2945cc0639%5C%22%3EThe%20city%20is%20relatively%20small%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20city%20is%20only%20about%201.5%20square%20miles.%20A%20housing%20sho